title: 820-01958 5v only
message:
Check R7900.
Also check diode mode to ground on the coils around U7800.

title: 820-01958 5v only
message: Maybe some crap under U7800 on the left side or under T2 chip?

title: 820-01958 5v only
message:
Sorry, I was looking at wrong schematic (01598).

You may have bad U7800, or accumulated crap underneath.
Try heating with quality flux.

title: 820-01958 5v only
message: Fluxed, heated and gave it a few little taps but no change unfortunately

title: 820-01958 5v only
message: Then you need to change U7800.

title: 820-01958 5v only
message:
With U7800 removed I'm still getting those low readings on diode mode. Could it be anything else before I order a U7800?

I expected it to alter the diode mode reading when removed

title: 820-01958 5v only
message:
The diode mode readings on the coils are not caused by U7800, but T2.
You should compare the values with good board.
